"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-athletics-european-athletics-championships-2024-keely-hodgkinson-olympics-b1164054.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Athletics  Despite having to return to her sickbed,Keely Hodgkinsonimmediately switched her attention to the Olympics aftersuccessfully defending her 800metre titleat theEuropean Athletics Championshipsin Rome on Wednesday night.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 440, \"end\": 444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.6346914492804332, \"rank\": 0.5741298109932549, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old had been confined to bed in the build-up to event and decided to run just 10 minutes before the final.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And while her winning time was three seconds off her personal best and just 0.14seconds ahead of the chasing pack, it was enough for Britain's clearest banker for gold.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.70608412382508, \"rank\": 0.41626173214020973, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ordinarily she would have allowed herself a celebration, but this time her plan was to head back to bed to recover as the long build-up to Paris continues.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999758984, \"rank\": 2.4246088558415577e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am super-excited for Paris,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999758984, \"rank\": 2.4246088558415577e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The next seven weeks are going to be incredible.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic Games are so special.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a huge opportunity to change your life and I am just ready to go for it.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel really confident.\\\"\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her win in such circumstances fired a warning shot to her rivals - notably Athing Mu, who has yet to compete at the highest level this season because of a hamstring injury, and Mary Moraa, who Hodgkinson has already beaten this season.\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9227368696221203, \"rank\": 0.08373257092197844, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's marathon world record holder banned after doping admission  Hunter Bell pips Hodgkinson to 800m silver at World Championships  Johnson-Thompson shares heptathlon bronze at World Championships  Reset your wellbeing for the year ahead  Both the victory and just running alone said a lot for the grit and determination of the Briton, who puffed out her cheeks in relief at the finishing line and then simply sat down expressionless.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Bell\", \"score\": 0.9999999999672582, \"rank\": 3.2706568267580493e-11, \"text\": \"Hunter Bell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Bell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Bell\"}, {\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.9227368696221203, \"rank\": 0.08373257092197844, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On reflection, she said: \\\"I was lying in bed thinking, 'Can I run?'\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been umming and ahing all day.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt a little bit of a sore throat and sniffles, and then it got worse.\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 2001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My whole body was achy and I had a headache.\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had vitamin C, aspiring, nose spray, paracetamol.\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have just done all I can to get rid of it.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I only decided to run 10 minutes before the call room, so I am quite proud of myself for going on the start line and really attacking the gold, given the circumstances.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think I would have been disappointed if I did not give it a go.\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had a title to defend and I really wanted to do it.\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the worst I have felt in a race, but it was just about finding a way to win.\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If they were going to beat me, they had to catch me.\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had to believe in the fact that I am the defending champion.\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When I finished, it was just relief.\\\"\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It proved a double golden night for Britain, as the women's 4x100m relay team of Dina Asher-Smith, Desiree Henry, Amy Hunt and Daryll Neita took top honours.\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.70608412382508, \"rank\": 0.41626173214020973, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2759, \"end\": 2775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dina Asher-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 2777, \"end\": 2790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Desir\\u00e8e_Henry\", \"score\": 0.9999999897668204, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Desiree Henry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Desir\\u00e8e_Henry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Desir\\u00e8e_Henry\"}, {\"begin\": 2792, \"end\": 2800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Hunt\", \"score\": 0.9999915625723019, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amy Hunt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Hunt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Hunt\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daryll Neita\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daryll_Neita\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those two winning medals took a weakened team, devoid of many of its star turns so close to the Olympics, to third place overall in the table.\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4